Source: storage-engine
Section: database
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Ruohang Feng <rh@vonng.com>
Build-Depends: debhelper-compat (= 13), postgresql-all (>= 217~), liblz4-dev (>= 1), libzstd-dev (>= 1), libcurl4-openssl-dev (>= 7)
Standards-Version: 4.6.2
Rules-Requires-Root: no
Homepage: https://github.com/saulojb/storage_engine

Package: postgresql-PGVERSION-storage-engine
Architecture: any
Provides: postgresql-storage-engine
Depends: ${postgresql:Depends}, ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: Columnar and row-compressed table access methods for PostgreSQL
  storage_engine is a Hydra-derived PostgreSQL extension that provides
  two high-performance table access methods:
  colcompress for column-oriented analytics and rowcompress for
  row-oriented compressed storage.
  This package targets PostgreSQL PGVERSION.
